name: Ann Olave
text: We were early waited to get unloaded like 4 hours. Appointment at 6 still waiting.There's a little porta potty kind of hidden. It was clean thank goodness. Workers have passed us by several times and they have our paperwork! Update ---We got updated and are waiting for our turn still it's been 2 hours of waiting and we had to go ask questions.

name: Jane Summerlott
text:
I am not particularly fond of giving terrible ratings.
This receiver doesn't follow appointments.
Upon arrival nobody answered the call box, 45 minutes later someone arrived to get my bills.
2.5 hrs til I received a dock. It's now been 4.5 hrs no signs of unloading.
They don't care about HOS.
They Don't care about appointments, Except to charge you for being late
If you have the option Don't Come Here.
It smells,  no toilets,  nothing to benefit the drivers, and a call to enter gate.
The only driver they care about is  Estes,  tankers and day cabs who d/h.

name: Mike Goldman
text:

name: cynthia carver
text: Back in 88 I work for quality foods I love my job they took care of us then I live in Huntsville now but back then ran the pack out belt and it used to have a cook room they were good people  then.I  live in Huntsville now so I went to Walmart in Huntsville and I seen the quality package I didn’t like how the fingers look they were all crumbled up too much breading on them so yesterday I went and I seen them again they were awesome fingers were laid flat Beautiful fingers keep it up quality foods George Elrod was my boss and Mr. C he was a good man it was all about teamwork back then. Miss that place

name: Teresa Reeves
text:
OK FOODS  is doing a wonderful thing for their employees. I should know because it happened to me. Jan 07, 2019 I won a NEW CAR for perfect attendance. I am still speechless from the JOY I have about the win. I was the first winner, but there will be another. That's an incentive worth working for, don't you think? Hard work and dedication will pay off. AGAIN, Thank you OK FOODS. I Give a shout out to all of my fellow employees in Albertville Plant 1. YEE HAH!!! and God Bless you.
And for all who want to "down the place", its not Albertville Quality Foods anymore. It is proudly "OK FOODS" thank you.
